  "texts": [
    "In contrast, accuracy notably decreases when solely relying on the MLLM-generated captions (average accuracy drops to 65.1%), highlighting that inaccuracies or hallucinations introduced by the MLLM significantly impair the effectiveness of the subsequent LLM-based candidate selection step.",
    "Moreover, integrating global captions into query-based captioning (Caption → Query+Caption) shows intermediate performance (average accuracy 85.0%), suggesting global captions provide valuable contextual constraints yet still introduce noise due to multimodal hallucinations.",
    "These findings underscore the importance of accurate textual inputs in our reasoning framework and identify improving caption generation as a critical avenue for future research.",
    "In summary, our ablation experiments confirm the robustness of the proposed candidate generation pipeline, clearly indicating that performance bottlenecks primarily originate from MLLM-generated captions rather than the reasoning mechanism itself.",
    "Stability Across Independent RunsTo evaluate the robustness of our training-free pipeline, we conduct three independent runs across the RefCOCO, Re-fCOCO+, and RefCOCOg benchmarks."
  ],
